What I have found is that in 90% of the times it does NOT stick on all 4 mobs. <br>
Ok, then just round them up. IMO, easier said than done. This takes time, and mana to resnare. then more time to reround the mobs up. By the time they are all in a nice snared group our crappy snare breaks. Gaaah!  <br>
So, I decided to just try it the hardcore way: full-speed kiting! Sure, it takes longer time between casts, and the margins are much smaller, but when I have finished a kite most of the time I have 1-2 bubs of mana left meaning good margins and less total downtime. <br>
The trick to this is to start running again just when the spell timer gets down to 0. you will hit the mobs just a few meters behind you but wont get hit yourself if you start casting at max range. <br>
Oh and I dont use the SotF either, i admit it would be VERY useful for pulling, but Ive been to lazy to do the quest yet. Judging distance is easily done by having you level 1 spell memmed and hotkeyed. <br>
<br>
Well, just my view on quadding, Im having fun with it =)<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/umaultar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Maultar</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_bluespot.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/21/01 5:30:37 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Ok this sounds crazy, but WHY ever use BoF...?</span><hr size=1> I am 53 now and been quadding wyverns in CS.  I read once to use BoF rather that atols for less mana and it works better..... It has for me.  I almost always get BoF to work on all 4 everytime.  If not leave snares ones behind and bring unsnared ahead snare them then combine 4 and resnare and resnare again if one missed.  Always same order from top to bottom....<br>
<br>
Snared<br>
Snared<br>
Resisted<br>
Snared<br>
<br>
Then resnare until 3rd is snared then you know you ok.  I then Pillar of Frost them and still have mana left over and no I don't have insane mana items.  I guess quadding gets easier as you are older.  Hell with Pillar of lightning wyverns will be very easy.  I also stopped quadding at 34 after I left loio. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uarmok.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Armok</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/21/01 9:12:10 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Ok this sounds crazy, but WHY ever use BoF...?</span><hr size=1> There are some mobs that you can easily quad kite with sow -- aviaks and spectres come to mind -- but there are also many, especially at the higher levels, where BoF or Atols are absolutely necessary.  These include any giants, wyverns (because the kiting space is a bit tight), and raptors (VERY tight quarters on the isle).<br>
<br>
You'll probably notice fewer fizzles and resists as you grow in levels.  Note that some players stick with BoF, and others prefer Atols.   Both are good spells and have advantages and disadvantages, while personally I always used Atols.<br>
<br>
- Armok Komra &lt;Triton&gt;<br>
Sorcerer of Povar <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/udrednoct.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Drednoct</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/21/01 10:45:26 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Ok this sounds crazy, but WHY ever use BoF...?</span><hr size=1> Hey, if you can quad without snaring, then more power to ya. Snaring just makes it easier and safer. And just in case something goes wrong, you have enough time to gate before the mobs get to you. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uvespid.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Vespid</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/21/01 11:22:55 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://ns.iicanada.com/scott/ves-pimp2.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Ok this sounds crazy, but WHY ever use BoF...?</span><hr size=1> Snaring is also helpful to those around you when things go wrong (e.g. if you die, or accidentally aggro someone). <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uetnu.showPublicProfile?language=EN>etnu</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Channeler</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/22/01 10:50:55 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.geocities.com/fekkin_rar/smileysex.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Ok this sounds crazy, but WHY ever use BoF...?</span><hr size=1> You can do this with any normal speed running mob and a 5.0 or less cast time AE (All pillars, Circle of Force)<br>
<br>
That's how I do it. <p>"Wait, I suggest you go play a druid, the class Verant invented so that even retards could play"</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uennyaorcsbane.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ennya Orcsbane</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/24/01 12:55:44 pm)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Ok this sounds crazy, but WHY ever use BoF...?</span><hr size=1> Ulthorks have been giving me 2-3 blue of EXP per pull for the last few levels, (36-40) and one in 40. A few times when BoF wore off and there were still mobs chasing me I had to make a choice: BoF and try to get more mana -XOR- one last CoF that shold kill them all...<br>
<br>
Almost every time I choose CoF I died under a rain of about 1000 damage.<br>
<br>
If you can get the spell off fast enough, go for it, but I would choose a CSAE not an AoE for that last shot. preferably one with a big Knockback : ) <p>Ennya Orcsbane<BR>
1st Elder of The Tears Of Veeshan<BR>
Learned Slayer, WurmSlayer<BR>
Assigner of the Hunt<BR>
Wizardess<BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uammeroutcaster.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ammer Outcaster</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/24/01 7:04:23 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Reason for BoF</span><hr size=1> Another reason for BoF is later on, obviously cast times go up. Conflageration is a 5.5 second cast correct me if I'm wrong anyway, that margin between you and your mob isn't there. As most of you know our DD's don't typically go very far range wise but, our bolts do. Anyway, just cast times get longer so BoF does help, I think for the most part. At 5.5 seconds casting, giving yourself a second after running you're around 6.5-7 seconds and your mob is probably on top of you kicking your ass without BoF. I'd imagine that anyway. I've personally never tried kiting without BoF because I think it's great, works nice with jboots <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> . Well, good lucking kiting!<br>
<br>
--------------------<br>
Ammer Outcaster<br>
Erudite Wizard of the 46th Flame<br>
Guildless on Luclin server <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uapokkberzerk.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Apokk Berzerk</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/27/01 10:17:46 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Reason for BoF</span><hr size=1> I keep trying to stick with Atol's but I always come back to BoF for 2 reasons:<br>
<br>
1: Atol's ALWAYS fizzles.  This is a real pain cause a fizzle wastes mana and you now have to run more to gain the distance lost from your first attempt to snare<br>
<br>
2: Uses twice the mana.  120mana isn't a big deal, but if one of the 4 resists your snare while quadding, you just wasted 240mana on snares, ouch!<br>
<br>
 <p><html>
<img src="http://142.55.42.238/apokk.jpg"></img>
</html>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/utalamanthalon.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Talamanthalon</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/28/01 7:35:40 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Reason for BoF</span><hr size=1> The reason is, the cast time on your AoE that you use to nuke is shorter then the new one you get at lvl 34 COF.  You can aoe the sarnies and stuff full speed because of the shorter casting time.  When you start using lvl 34 COF you have a VERY VERY VERY small amount of time to wait for the COF to go off and have enough time to get away.  I was doing this at 34 on the hunters (full speed kiting them) and I got smacked around much more then I ever did with the LOIO mobs.  IMO you'll soon realize that bof will be necessary for most mobs when you start using COF to kite. <p>Talamanthalon Quevloth
<br>
Blaster of the 40th Circle
<br>
Terris Thule Server
<br>
Master Taxi
<br>
<br>
Lyricsbane Blazingharp 
<br>
20th lvl Master Runner
<br>
Bard of the Screeching Harp
<br>
Terris Thule Server
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ufirion69.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Firion69</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/29/01 11:50:16 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Reason for BoF</span><hr size=1> Actually, Thalamanthalon, youre right =(<br>
<br>
Dire wolves are easy to quad full speed but i guess Thorks have longer range or something, cause I always get smacked by them =(  On the other hand i did learn how to use BoF, so its not really that big a problem. at level 40 with 200 int and 150+managear  the snaremana is ok to waste.<br>
